node.title: South Australia announces four new COVID-19 infections including mystery case
node.alt: A carpark and building with a tall black sign saying Goodlife Health Clubs
node.description: SA Health is boosting COVID testing in Adelaide's southern suburbs after a mystery infection was one of four new cases reported today.
node.content:
["SA Health is boosting COVID testing in Adelaide's southern suburbs after a mystery infection was one of four new cases reported today.", "SA Health said the mystery case spent time in the Port Noarlunga region, and has urged anyone in the area to get tested if they have any symptoms and isolate until they receive a negative result.", "Two of the cases are interstate travellers and the fourth case,\u00a0who attended the high school reunion super-spreader event in Norwood, is under investigation to determine if they caught their infection interstate or in South Australia.", "The cases include three men aged between 20 and 70, and one woman in her thirties who tested positive after\u00a0travelling to the Northern Territory.", "That case prompted the Territory to impose seven days of home quarantine\u00a0for all travellers from South Australia.", "Yesterday, Western Australian Premier Mark McGowan announced his state's borders\u00a0would close to South Australians, except for approved travellers.", "New exposure sites were announced this morning, including Goodlife Health Club Marion which was named a close contact site.", "You can find information on testing site hours and the nearest site to you on the SA Health\u00a0website.", "
South Australians line up to be tested
", "A man who attended the Henley High School reunion on Saturday night lined up at a COVID-19 testing site\u00a0this morning but said he had so far tested negative.", "\"I've spoken to a few people [who were also there] and they're all pretty fine,\" he said.", "\"Some are in Tom's Court.\"", "The man said he was feeling well, with no\u00a0symptoms yet.", "He said he was feeling \"relaxed\" about the whole situation.", "\"I guess it was bound to happen really, wasn't it?\" he said.", "\"It's all happened pretty much all at once.", "\"It was a COVID-Safe event, with a QR code, there was less than 50 people in a large hall.\"", "", "
Cars line up at South Australian testing sites.(ABC News: Natasha Thiele)
", "One woman, who had attended a Largs North cafe on Monday, found out from a friend on Thursday night that it had been listed as an exposure site.", "She said she and her husband, who also got tested, \"had been here before\" after returning from travel.", "\"We thought we'd be early [for testing], because we know what it's like,\" she said.", "\"We've been here before and had to wait six hours.\""]
